hammer.api

Interface Container.StrictBinder<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to configure
    Enclosing interface:
    Container

    public static interface Container.StrictBinder<T>
    A Container.StrictBinder is a configuration entity used to used to configure the binding of an implementation type or instance that has been added to a Container and bind it to a specific injectable type or set of injectable types.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Container.QualifierBinder forItself()
      Binds the configured implementation type or instance to injection requests for its own concrete type.

      Binds the configured implementation type or instance to injection requests for the given specific injection types.

    • Method Detail

      • forItself

        Container.QualifierBinder forItself()
        Binds the configured implementation type or instance to injection requests for its own concrete type. This is the default binding.
        Returns:
        a Container.QualifierBinder used to further configure the binding

      • forSpecificTypes

        Container.QualifierBinder forSpecificTypes(Class<? super T>... types)
        Binds the configured implementation type or instance to injection requests for the given specific injection types.
        Parameters:
        types - the types to bind
        Returns:
        a Container.QualifierBinder used to further configure the binding
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a supplied type conflicts with a previously bound type and multi bindings are NOT configured for that type

      • forSpecificTypes

        Container.QualifierBinder forSpecificTypes(TypeToken<? super T>... types)
        Binds the configured implementation type or instance to injection requests for the given specific injection types.
        Parameters:
        types - the types to bind
        Returns:
        a Container.QualifierBinder used to further configure the binding
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a supplied type conflicts with a previously bound type and multi bindings are NOT configured for that type
